SIMPLE: gradate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gradate
<hw>Gra"date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Grade</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To grade or arrange (parts in a
whole, colors in painting, etc.), so that they shall
harmonize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>To bring to a certain strength or
grade of concentration; <as>as, to gradate a saline
solution</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gradation</ent>⟦br⟧
